description: From Latin inauspicatus; prefix in- (“not”) + auspicatus, past participle auspicari. Equivalent to in- +‎ auspicate.

adjectives.description: inauspicate (comparative more inauspicate, superlative most inauspicate)

examples: And this was the successe of his first invasion, which though it bore an inauspicate face, it proved of a friendly event
